        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 20 at 4:15PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Timpas, or 11 miles southwest of La Junta, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
La Junta, North La Junta, and Higbee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
